DStv and GOtv customers on the lower packages; DStv Yanga and GOtv Jolli can now look forward to the English Premier League match between Arsenal and Manchester United today Top English Premier League matches usually air on the higher DStv and GOtv packages, so this is definitely a great treat for the Gunners or Red Devils fans on the lower packages. Both teams are in a three-way race with Tottenham Hotspur for the final Champions league berth – the fourth position on the league table.   Tottenham held by Brentford to dent top-four hopes     Arsenal beat Man United to boost top-four hopes     Pogba: My career with Man Utd not over   Tottenham and Arsenal are currently placed 4th  and 5th  on the league table. Though the North London bitter rivals are tied on 57 points from 32 games, Tottenham has a superior goal difference of 18 to Arsenal’s 10. Manchester United on the other hand has played one more match than both teams, yet they trail by three points and are in danger of missing out on Europe’s premier competition. The winner of this crunch tie at the Emirates Stadium showing on SuperSport Football (DStv channel 205 and GOtv channel 31) at 12:30pm will get a significant boost in the top four race as the season draws near to a close. To view this game, download the MyDStv or MyGOtv apps to subscribe, upgrade or set up auto renewal to stay connected without interruptions.